OL,3,CFirst cases of bluetongue found in
OL,4,Csheep in Wales
OL,6,FThis is the first time Bluetongue-3
OL,7,Fhas been found in Wales and follows
OL,8,FBTV-3 cases being detected in the east
OL,9,Fof England over the last month.
OL,11,FFarmers are being urged to be vigilant
OL,12,Ffor the disease and practice safe
OL,13,Fsourcing of livestock.
OL,15,FBluetongue is caused by a virus that
OL,16,Fis primarily transmitted by certain
OL,17,Fspecies of biting midges. It affects
OL,18,Fruminants (such as cattle, goats,
OL,19,Fsheep and deer) and camelids (such as
OL,20,Falpacas and llamas).
