OL,3,CFirst cases of bluetongue found in
OL,4,Csheep in Wales
OL,6,FBluetongue does not affect people or
OL,7,Ffood safety.Further investigations are
OL,8,Ftaking place on the farm affected to
OL,9,Fdetermine whether additional controls
OL,10,Fare needed.
OL,12,FThe Deputy Chief Veterinary Officer
OL,13,FGavin Watkins said: "The cases
OL,14,Fidentified in Gwynedd are from animals
OL,15,Fbrought into Wales."We will apply
OL,16,Fmeasures to stop the disease spreading
OL,17,Ffrom these three sheep and our aim
OL,18,Fremains to keep Wales free of
OL,19,Fbluetongue."
